Params: When you burst into the library where Noan is, the Babylonia sky has already transitioned into the hues of night.
You got caught red-handed by Celica while you were negotiating with a merchant on the roadside because your year-end summary report was late for three whole days.
Noan! I need to take shelter here!
Without question, Noan immediately steps aside, gesturing toward a corner of the library's beverage bar.
Call me after Celica has gone far enough...
This place might not be safe if it's Celica.
He pushes open the narrow door to the storage room behind the bar and opens the box deep inside.
As anticipated, Celica's voice soon echoes through the library.
Her footsteps echo throughout the library, searching the bar counter just as Noan anticipated.
【kuroname】, no matter how many missions you have on your plate, that report can't be delayed any longer. After all, it needs to be presented at the Parliament.
【kuroname】? If you come out now, you still have a chance to finish it in the battle preparation room.
But if I find you... you'll have to complete it alone in a meeting room inaccessible even to Gray Raven.
After circling the library twice, Celica sighs—then, the familiar sound of an emergency terminal call rings.
But... your terminal is not with you?!
Seems like the commandant left it here... I'll return it later.
How could the commandant possibly leave the terminal here?
Their voices begin to fade, drowned by the clamor of the bustling crowd beyond.
Ten minutes later, Celica's footsteps finally peter out.
A crack in the box reveals Noan standing there, a smile gracing his face.
...Indeed, I'm not done with the report yet.
It's not just that—but I've bought you some time.
Let me lend a hand with that report before they catch you here, Commandant.
